included.summary:
View my portfolio: www.bayannada.com 
I am a motivated and energetic professional seeking an entry level UX Research position at a growing company that utilizes my knowledge and experience and will enable me to contribute to the advancement and success of the organization. 
I obtained my MS degree in Human Factors and Ergonomics Engineering from San Jose State University, and have extensive knowledge and expertise pertaining to user centered design and research approaches & methods, study design and implementation, and statistical analysis. Additionally I have extensive experience in blending leadership, human factors principles, cognitive and physical ergonomic principles, behavioral analysis, & psychological principles to drive the evaluation, enhancement, and redesign of systems and devices.
included.headline: User Experience Researcher at SAP Ariba

included.description: Using a 2x2 between-subject design to examine the effects of accent (Standard American English vs. Arab) and performance level (average vs. high) of hypothetical female employee on suitability rating, promotion decisions, and personal attributes. Two personality traits, openness to experience and need for cognition, were also explored to see if it would moderate the relationship. Results showed that performance level had an effect on the suitability rating and Arab accented employee was perceived as less competent.
included.title: Effects of Foreign Accent and Performance Level on Promotion Decisions and Suitability Rating
